%N A394568 Numbers k such that every m that is a solution to phi(m) = k is a totient number.
%C A394568 A subsequence of A143510.
%H A394568 Miles Englezou, <a href="/A394568/b394568.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..53</a>
%H A394568 Max Alekseyev, <a href="https://oeis.org/wiki/User:Max_Alekseyev/gpscripts">PARI/GP Scripts for Miscellaneous Math Problems</a> (invphi.gp).
%e A394568 269484032 is a term since phi^-1(269484032) = {541073408, 574890496, 676341760, 718613120, 811610112, 862335744, 1014512640, 1077919680}, and every such element is a totient number.
%o A394568 (PARI) isok(n) = vecprod(apply(x -> istotient(x), invphi(n)))==1 \\ using _Max Alekseyev_'s invphi.gp; see link.
%Y A394568 Cf. A002202, A143510, A387221.
